topic.title: CPU Subsystem Abstract

body.p: The CPU subsystem enables configuration and control of the device. Firmware executed on the embedded ARM Cortex-A9 MPCore dual-core processor performs various functions such as device configuration, interrupt handling, consequential actions, and PMON transfers. The SDK software on the external host communicates with the embedded processor firmware at run-time using message passing over a PCI Express (PCIe) Gen2 x1 lane endpoint interface.
